INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('35827', '4', 'Heat Dutch oven over high heat until oil shimmers.'),
('35827', '5', 'Add sofrito, alcaparrado (or pimiento-stuffed olives), salt, pepper, and cumin. Cook, stirring often, until liquid boils away, and mixture starts to sizzle, about 5 minutes.'),
('35827', '6', 'Add smoked pork. Stir well, then add rice and stir to evenly coat rice with oil.'),
('35827', '7', 'Add the pigeon peas, broth, and enough water to cover rice by an inch and a half.'),
('35827', '8', 'Bring mixture to boil over high heat without stirring.'),
('35827', '9', 'Let boil until liquid meets level of rice. Cover Dutch oven, reduce the heat to low, and cook 20 minutes without opening lid.'),
('35827', '10', 'Stir rice, fluff with fork, and serve.'),
('35828', '1', 'Place the lentils in a medium-size bowl. Fill the bowl halfway with water and rinse the lentils by rubbing them between your fingertips. The water will become cloudy.'),
('35828', '2', 'Drain this water. Repeat three or four times, until the water remains relatively clear. drain. Now fill the bowl halfway with warm water and let it sit at room temperature, covered, until the lentils have softened, at least 30 minutes (you can let them soak longer, but no longer than 4 hours).'),
('35828', '3', 'Drain the lentils.'),
('35828', '4', 'Pour  cup water into a blender jar, add the lentils, and puree, scraping the inside of the jar as needed, until the mixture is smooth and paste-like.'),
('35828', '5', 'Transfer the thick batter to the same medium-size bowl.'),
('35828', '6', 'Pour about 1 cup water into the blender jar and run the blender to wash out any remnants of batter. add this to the batter in the bowl. Stir another 1 cup water into the batter, and add the rice, yogurt, and salt.'),
('35828', '7', 'Whisk thoroughly to create a homogenous, if gritty, blend. Stir in the Eno, which will instantly aerate the batter, making it bubble and appear fermented.'),
('35828', '8', 'If you dont have an idli pan, you will need to create one: Set a standard muffin tin (with cups 2 to 3 inches wide and 1 to 1 inches deep) in a larger flameproof baking pan. Lightly spray the muffin cups with cooking spray. Fill the cups three-quarters full with the idli batter.'),
('35828', '9', 'Pour boiling water into the baking pan so it reaches halfway up the sides of the muffin tin. Cover the entire baking pan tightly with aluminum foil, and set it on a burner over medium heat. Steam for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a toothpick or knife stuck in an idli comes clean.'),
('35828', '10', 'Remove the muffin tin from the hot water bath and allow it to cool for at least 5 minutes. Then slide the idlis out, giving them a nudge with a butter knife. Repeat with the remaining batter.'),
('35828', '11', 'If you do own an idli pan, spray the individual concave disks with cooking spray and fill them three-quarters full with batter. Stack them (there are usually 4 plates with 4 concave-shaped discs on each plate) around the idli stand, placing the small metal rods between the plates to separate them. set the device in a large stockpot filled with hot water to a depth of about  inch. Cover, and steam over medium-high heat until a toothpick or knife stuck in an idli comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.'),
('35828', '12', 'Remove the idli stand from the stockpot and allow it to cool for at least 5 minutes. Then slide the idlis out, giving them a nudge with a butter knife. Repeat with the remaining batter.'),
('35828', '13', 'Serve the idlis in individual serving bowls, with the pigeon pea stew ladled on top.'),
('35828', '14', 'var article'),
('35828', '15', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('35828', '16', 'article'),
('35828', '17', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('35829', '1', 'Cook and stir first 5 ingredients in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 min. or until vegetables are crisp-tender.'),
('35829', '2', 'Add water, peas, tomato sauce and seasonings. stir.  Bring to boil.'),
('35829', '3', 'Stir in rice. cover.  Simmer on medium-low heat 20 min. or until rice is tender.'),
('35830', '1', 'Place the pigeon peas in a medium-size bowl. Fill the bowl halfway with water and rinse the peas by rubbing them between your fingertips. The water will become cloudy.'),
('35830', '2', 'Drain this water. Repeat three or four times, until the water remains relatively clear. drain. Now fill the bowl halfway with warm water and add the chiles to the peas. Allow the peas and chiles to soften by letting them sit at room temperature, covered, for at least 30 minutes or up to 4 hours.'),
('35830', '3', 'Drain the pigeon peas and chiles, transfer them to a food processor, and process to form a red-speckled, slightly gritty paste. Scrape this paste into a medium-size bowl. Fold in the yellow split peas, onion, cilantro, salt, and asafetida, forming a paste that looks like wet sand.'),
('35830', '4', 'Grease your palms with a little cooking oil or spray. Take a heaping tablespoon of the paste and shape it into a tight round ball. Press the ball between the palms of your hands to form a patty roughly 1 inches in diameter and  inch thick. Lay it on a plate or tray. Repeat with the remaining paste. You should end up with about 25 patties.'),
('35830', '5', 'Pour oil to a depth of 2 to 3 inches into a wok, Dutch oven, or medium-size saucepan.'),
('35830', '6', 'Heat the oil over medium heat until a candy or deep-fry thermometer inserted into the oil (without touching the pans bottom) registers 350F. (An alternative way to see if the oil is at the right temperature for deep-frying is to gently flick a drop of water over it. If the pearl-like drop skitters across the surface, the oil is ready.)'),
('35830', '7', 'Line a large plate or a cookie sheet with several layers of paper towels. Once the oil is ready, gently slide 8 patties into the pan (do not crowd the pan). Fry, turning them occasionally, until they are caramel-brown and crisp on both sides, about 5 minutes.'),
('35830', '8', 'Remove them with a slotted spoon and place them on the paper-towel-lined plate to drain. Repeat until all the patties are fried. You may need to adjust the heat to maintain the oils temperature at 350F.'),
('35830', '9', 'To make the sauce, whisk the yogurt, salt, and  cup water together in a medium-size bowl.'),
('35830', '10', 'Heat the oil in a small skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('35830', '11', 'Add the mustard seeds, cover the skillet, and wait until the seeds have stopped popping (not unlike popcorn), about 30 seconds. Immediately add the tomato, chiles, and cilantro. Cook, uncovered, until the tomato has broken down and formed a chunky sauce, 2 to 4 minutes. Stir this spicy sauce into the watered-down yogurt.'),
('35830', '12', 'Place 2 fritters on each individual serving plate, and cover each one with a heaping teaspoon of the tart-hot, mustard-spiked yogurt sauce.'),
('35831', '1', 'Cook bacon, onion and sofrito sauce base in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 min. or until bacon is almost crisp.'),
('35831', '2', 'Add chicken to skillet. brown on all sides.'),
('35831', '3', 'Stir tomato sauce and broth into skillet. bring to boil.'),
('35831', '4', 'Add rice and pigeon peas.  Bring to boil. cover.'),
('35831', '5', 'Reduce heat to low. simmer 20 min. or until chicken is cooked through and rice is tender.  Sprinkle with cheese before serving.'),
('35832', '1', 'Place a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.'),
('35832', '2', 'Add the oil and bacon. Fry, stirring, until the bacon is crisp.'),
('35832', '3', 'Add the onion and cilantro. Continue to cook for 5 minutes until the onion is soft.'),
('35832', '4', 'Add the rice, tomatoes, oregano, cumin, salt, achiote, and pigeon peas. Cook for 5 to 7 minutes until the rice is opaque. Stir in the tomato paste and water and bring to boil. When all the water is absorbed, cover tightly and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 25 to 30 minutes until tender.'),
('35832', '5', 'Serve on a decorative platter and garnish with cilantro.'),
('35833', '1', 'Cook bacon in large skillet on medium-high heat 5 min. or until crisp.'),
('35833', '2', 'Remove bacon from skillet, reserving 1 Tbsp. of the drippings in skillet.'),
('35833', '3', 'Drain bacon on paper towels. set aside.'),
('35833', '4', 'Place tomatoes in blender.'),
('35833', '5', 'Add water. blend until tomatoes are smooth.  Cook reserved drippings until heated through. stir in tomato sauce.'),
('35833', '6', 'Add rice and pigeon peas. stir.  Bring to boil. cover. Reduce heat to low. simmer 20 min. or until rice is tender.'),
('35833', '7', 'Meanwhile, add chicken, skin-sides up, to large nonstick skillet. cover. Cook 5 min.. turn chicken. Cook, uncovered, an additional 7 to 9 min. or until chicken is cooked through and skins are golden brown.'),
('35833', '8', 'Mix annatto paste, mayo and garlic.'),
('35833', '9', 'Stir bacon into rice mixture. spoon onto serving plate. Top with chicken and annatto sauce.'),
('35834', '1', 'Put the pigeon peas, bay leaves, and garlic in a large pot, cover with 3 quarts of cold water, and place over medium heat. Cover and cook the beans until tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Check the water periodically. add more, if necessary, to keep the peas covered.'),
('35834', '2', 'Drain the pigeon peas and reserve 4 cups of the cooking liquid.'),
('35834', '3', 'Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F.'),
('35834', '4', 'Coat a large Dutch oven or other ovenproof pot with the achiote oil and place over medium heat. When the oil begins to smoke, add the onion, minced garlic, and peppers. Cook, stirring, for 10 minutes, until the vegetables have softened, without letting them brown. Stir in the cumin, coriander, and cayenne.'),
('35834', '5', 'Mix in the rice and stir.'),
('35834', '6', 'Add the reserved pigeon peas cooking liquid and stir.'),
('35834', '7', 'Add the peas, salt and lime juice. Top with a lid and place into the oven. Continue to cook until the liquid is evaporated, about 20 to 30 minutes, until the rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed.'),
('35834', '8', 'To make the achiote oil, pour the oil and achiote seeds in a pot or skillet. Cook over medium-low heat for 5 to 10 minutes. the oil will be reddish-orange from the achiote. Strain the oil and discard the achiote seeds.'),
('35838', '1', 'Wash dal in several changes of water until water runs clear and drain well in a sieve. Cook dal at a bare simmer in 1 1/2 cups water in a 3-quart saucepan until most of water is evaporated and dal has consistency of a paste, 40 to 45 minutes, stirring frequently during last 15 minutes to prevent scorching.'),
('35838', '2', 'Heat ghee in a 6-quart heavy saucepan over moderately high heat until hot but not smoking, then cook mustard seeds and red chile, stirring, until seeds begin to pop.'),
('35838', '3', 'Add 1 1/2 cups water and remaining ingredients (but not dal paste). Bring to a boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are softened, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('35838', '4', 'Add dal paste and remaining cup water, stirring to incorporate. Bring rasam to a boil, stirring occasionally, and season with salt.'),
('35839', '1', 'Preheat oven to 300 degrees F.'),
('35839', '2', 'Cut off 2-slices (about 1/4-cup) of pork and set aside for Spanish rice.'),
('35839', '3', 'Make at least 12-slits in pork with the tip of a very sharp knife. Put 1 clove of garlic in each slit. In a small bowl, mix together the sazon and adobo seasonings.'),
('35839', '4', 'Add 1/4-cup sofrito and stir together. Rub over entire pork shoulder.'),
('35839', '5', 'Place pork in large roasting pan, wrap with foil and cook for 3 hours.'),
('35839', '6', 'Remove the foil and crank oven up to 400 degrees F and let cook additional 20 minutes until desired crispness.'),
('35841', '1', 'Melt butter in a large, heavy saucepan over medium high heat.'),
('35841', '2', 'Place bacon in the saucepan, and cook until evenly brown. Stir in onion and celery, and cook until tender.'),
('35841', '3', 'Mix in tomato, tomato paste, and ketchup. Season with salt and pepper. Reduce heat to low, and continue cooking about 15 minutes.'),
('35841', '4', 'Stir pigeon peas and their liquid, water, rice, and thyme into the saucepan. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce heat. Cook 40 minutes on low, or until all liquid is absorbed. Fluff rice with a fork.'),
('35842', '1', 'Cook bacon in medium saucepan until crisp.'),
('35842', '2', 'Remove bacon from pan, reserving drippings in saucepan.'),
('35842', '3', 'Drain bacon on paper towels.'),
('35842', '4', 'Add green peppers, onions and garlic to reserved drippings. cook and stir on medium heat 5 min.'),
('35842', '5', 'Add tomato sauce, rice and black pepper. mix well. Stir in water.  Bring to boil.  Stir in peas. cover.  Simmer on medium-low heat 20 min.  Stir.'),
('35842', '6', 'Crumble bacon. sprinkle over rice mixture.'),
('35844', '1', 'Heat dressing in large skillet on medium-high heat.'),
('35844', '2', 'Add meat. cook 2 min. or until browned.'),
('35844', '3', 'Remove meat from skillet. set aside.  Keep warm.'),
('35844', '4', 'Add rice and ham to skillet. Cook 2 min., stirring occasionally. Stir in water and seasoning mix.  Bring to boil. cover.  Reduce heat to low. cook 15 min. or until rice is tender.'),
('35844', '5', 'Stir in meat, pigeon peas and tomatoes. cover.  Cook 5 to 10 min. or until heated through. Top with sour cream before serving.'),
('35847', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the pigeon peas and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil over high heat, and boil for minute.'),
('35847', '2', 'Remove the pan from the heat, cover tightly, and let stand for 1 hour. (Or soak the beans overnight in a large bowl with enough cold water to cover by 1 inch.)'),
('35847', '3', 'Drain the peas and return them to the medium saucepan with enough fresh water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil over high heat, reduce the heat to low, and simmer until the peas are tender, about 1 hour.'),
('35847', '4', 'Drain again.'),
('35847', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a 5-quart Dutch oven or soup kettle, bring the corned beef, ham hock, and water to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to low, and simmer until the meat is tender, about 1 hours.'),
('35847', '6', 'Drain the meat, reserving both the meat and the cooking liquid.'),
('35847', '7', 'Remove the meat from the ham hock and chop it coarsely. discard the bones.'),
('35847', '8', 'In a 5-quart Dutch oven or soup kettle, heat the oil over medium heat.'),
('35847', '9', 'Add the onion, scallions, garlic, and chile pepper. Cook, stirring often, until the onion has softened, about 4 minutes. Then stir in the tomatoes, tomato paste, chives, and thyme, breaking up the tomatoes with a spoon. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to low, and simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('35847', '10', 'Stir in the eggplant, calabaza, and white yam and cook for 5 minutes, stirring often. Stir in the reserved meat cooking liquid and the meat. Bring to a boil, reduce the heat to low, and simmer, stirring often, until the vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes. Stir in the cooked pigeon peas and the spinach, and cook until the spinach has wilted, about 5 minutes. Season with the pepper, depending on the hotness of the chile pepper'),
('35847', '11', 'Serve immediately.'),
('35847', '12', 'var article'),
('35847', '13', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('35847', '14', 'article'),
('35847', '15', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('35848', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('35848', '2', 'Preheat a 7 1/4-quart Dutch oven on medium-high heat, then melt butter and add oil. Season chicken generously with salt and pepper and sear until golden on both sides, about 8 minutes.'),
('35848', '3', 'Remove from pot and set aside.'),
('35848', '4', 'Add carrots, onion, celery, and apple, the whole habanero, garlic, bay leaves, and thyme. Season with salt and pepper and saute until they start to soften, about 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('35848', '5', 'Add wine and let reduce by half, scraping up any brown bits remaining on the bottom of the pot. Nestle chicken into pot and add enough broth to almost cover the chicken, about 1 1/2 cups and the gravy sauce. Cover and simmer for 1 hour 45 minutes or until chicken falls off the bone. In the last half hour, remove the lid and let liquid reduce.'),
('35848', '6', 'To make the gravy: In a medium saucepan, melt butter with oil over medium high-heat.'),
('35848', '7', 'Add giblets and brown on all sides, about 6 minutes.'),
('35848', '8', 'Add onion and continue cooking another 5 minutes, until onions start to soften.'),
('35848', '9', 'Add flour and stir, cooking another 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('35848', '10', 'Whisk in the stock. Bring to a simmer and strain. Discard giblets and put gravy back in the pot. Season with salt and pepper. Keep warm on the stove and add to braised chicken once it''s cooked.'),
('35848', '11', 'Serve Braised Chicken over Coconut Rice n'' Peas'),
('35848', '12', 'Heat olive oil in a medium pot over medium-high heat.'),
('35848', '13', 'Add onions and salt and saute, until onion becomes translucent and tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('35848', '14', 'Add rice and saute another 2 minutes to toast rice.'),
('35848', '15', 'Add coconut milk and fill saucepan with enough water to cover the rice by 1/2-inch or measure by placing your thumb tip on the rice and filling the pot with water until the water reaches the middle of your thumbnail. Bring rice to a simmer, cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid has evaporated, about 15 to 17 minutes.'),
('35848', '16', 'Remove from heat and let rice stand another 5 minutes, covered. Fluff rice with fork and then fold in pigeon peas. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.'),
('35866', '1', 'Prepare 3 cups rice with 2 regular-size bags of boil-in-bag rice cooked according to package directions.'),
('35866', '2', 'Remove rice from bag, and stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon ground ginger, and 1/2 teaspoon grated orange rind.'),
('35866', '3', 'Garnish with orange slices, if desired.'),
('35868', '1', 'Cook the rice pilaf according to the package directions. Meanwhile, in a medium skillet, over medium-high heat, cook the chorizo until just browned, 1 to 2 minutes.Stir into the pilaf along with the scallions before serving.'),
('35873', '1', 'Boil the tea, rice, and water in a small saucepan. Reduce heat to low. cover and simmer 20 minutes over low heat or until all the water is absorbed.'),
('35873', '2', 'Remove from heat. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, over low heat, stir the sugar, vinegar, and salt until dissolved. Fold into the cooked rice and serve.'),
('35874', '1', 'Rinse rice with cold running water 3 minutes or until water is no longer cloudy.'),
('35874', '2', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('35874', '3', 'Cook bacon in a 3 1/2-qt. saucepan over medium heat 10 minutes or until crisp.'),
('35874', '4', 'Drain and set bacon aside, reserving 2 Tbsp. bacon drippings in pan.'),
('35874', '5', 'Saut onion in hot drippings in saucepan over medium-high heat 8 minutes or until onion is tender. add garlic, and saut 1 minute.'),
('35874', '6', 'Stir in rinsed rice, chicken broth, and next 3 ingredients. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 30 minutes, stirring mixture every 7 to 10 minutes.'),
('35874', '7', 'Remove from heat. fluff with a fork. Stir in crumbled bacon and 3 Tbsp. parsley. garnish, if desired.'),
('35879', '1', 'Use short or medium-grain rice. Its more starchy and round than the long-grain variety, which just wont hold together well enough to support ingredients in sushi. Many stores now sell specifically-labeled sushi rice.'),
('35879', '2', 'Before you cook it, wash/rinse the rice until the water runs totally clearabout five or six times. If you dont thoroughly rinse the rice, itll end up in a big, sticky ball. Theres enough internal starch in the rice for it to sufficiently hold together for sushi, so get all the stuff on the outside off by rinsing well.'),
('35879', '3', 'Use a rice cooker/steamer. Rice made on the stovetop will not work for sushi. it wont be the right consistency. Rice cookers are widely available for as low as $12.'),
('35916', '1', 'Rinse beef, pat dry, and cut across the grain into 1/8-inch-thick slices about 3 inches long. In a small bowl, mix beef with 1/4 cup Korean marinade.'),
('35916', '2', 'Remove and discard bean stem ends and strings.'),
('35916', '3', 'Cut beans diagonally in 3-inch lengths.'),
('35916', '4', 'Cut carrot into matchstick-size pieces about 3 inches long.'),
('35916', '5', 'In a 14-inch wok or 12-inch frying pan over high heat, mix 1/2 cup water, beans, and carrot. Cover and stir occasionally just until tender to bite, about 3 minutes.'),
('35916', '6', 'Drain. immerse in cold water.'),
('35916', '7', 'Drain when cool. In a bowl, mix with vinegar, sesame oil, sugar, and salt to taste.'),
('35916', '8', 'Place wok over high heat. when hot, add salad oil.'),
('35916', '9', 'Add beef with liquid in bowl. stir until meat is no longer pink, about 2 minutes.'),
('35916', '10', 'Add remaining marinade and broth to pan. stir until boiling.'),
('35916', '11', 'Scoop rice into bowls. add beef and sauce, then vegetables and seasonings. Sprinkle with onions and sesame seed.'),
('35918', '1', 'Rinse rice with cold running water 3 minutes or until water is no longer cloudy.'),
('35918', '2', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('35918', '3', 'Cook bacon in a 3 1/2-qt. saucepan over medium heat 10 minutes or until crisp.'),
('35918', '4', 'Drain and set bacon aside, reserving 2 Tbsp. bacon drippings in pan.'),
('35918', '5', 'Saut onion in hot drippings in saucepan over medium-high heat 8 minutes or until onion is tender. add garlic, and saut 1 minute.'),
('35918', '6', 'Stir in rinsed rice, chicken broth, and next 3 ingredients. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 30 minutes, stirring mixture every 7 to 10 minutes.'),
('35918', '7', 'Remove from heat. fluff with a fork. Stir in crumbled bacon and 3 Tbsp. parsley. garnish, if desired.'),
('35919', '1', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('35919', '2', 'Add onions and cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Reduce heat to low and add rice and garlic. Stir constantly, making sure the rice doesnt burn. Cook over low heat for 3 minutes.'),
('35919', '3', 'Add Ro-tel and tomatoes. Stir to combine and let cook for 2 minutes. Finally, add broth and stir together.'),
('35919', '4', 'Add some kosher salt and a good teaspoon of cumin--more if you love cumin flavor! Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 10 to 15 additional minutes or until rice is done.'),
('35919', '5', 'Add more liquid as needed. rice shouldnt be sticky.Just before serving, sprinkle lots of freshly chopped cilantro over the top.'),
('35919', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('35923', '1', 'Heat a saut pan over medium-high heat. add 2 teaspoons olive oil.'),
('35923', '2', 'Add bell peppers, carrots, and red onion. cook 2 minutes. Microwave rice 5 minutes. transfer to a bowl.'),
('35923', '3', 'Add peas, radishes, 1 tablespoon fresh lime juice, and 1 tablespoon seasoned rice vinegar to rice. season with salt and pepper.'),
('35923', '4', 'Fab tip: Make the rice look like five-star fare by shaping it into a timbale. Use a clean tuna can or deep, round-shaped biscuit cutter coated with cooking spray to pack in 1 cup rice mixture. Turn it over onto the serving plate, and voil!'),
('35929', '1', 'Bring chicken broth to a boil in a medium saucepan.'),
('35929', '2', 'Add rice and seasonings. reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.'),
('35929', '3', 'Serve hot.'),
('35930', '1', 'Save Recipe'),
('35930', '2', 'Print Recipe'),
('35930', '3', 'Saffron Rice'),
('35930', '4', 'Ingredients2 pinches good quality saffron threads (spice)1 tbsp  extra virgin olive oil1 small yellow onion, minced (about 1/2 cup)2 cups white basmati rice3 3/4 cups chicken stock, or substitute water + extra pinch of salt1 tsp salt'),
('35930', '5', 'Total Time: 45 Minutes'),
('35930', '6', 'Servings: 8 side portions'),
('35930', '7', 'Kosher Key: Meat or Pareve (use salted water instead of stock for pareve)'),
('35934', '1', 'Slightly smash garlic clove using flat side of a knife. Stir together garlic, broth, butter, and salt in a large saucepan. bring to a boil over high heat. Stir in rice. reduce heat to low, and cook, covered, 20 minutes or until broth mixture is absorbed and rice is tender.'),
('35934', '2', 'Remove and discard garlic. stir in lemon rind using a fork.'),
('35934', '3', 'Lemon-Dill Rice: Proceed with recipe as directed, stirring 1 tsp. dried dill into cooked rice with lemon rind.'),
('35937', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil in a wok.'),
('35937', '2', 'Add the eggs and scramble lightly with a wooden spoon over high heat.'),
('35937', '3', 'Transfer the eggs to a plate.'),
('35937', '4', 'Add the remaining 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil to the wok. When the oil is hot, add the chiles, shallots, garlic and belacan and stir-fry over high heat until aromatic, about 2 minutes.'),
('35937', '5', 'Add the shrimp and stir-fry for 1 minute.'),
('35937', '6', 'Add the rice, reduce the heat to moderate and cook, stirring, until heated through, 3 to 4 minutes. sprinkle the rice with water as necessary to keep it moist. Stir the oyster sauce, soy sauce, white pepper and sugar into the rice. Stir in the scrambled eggs.'),
('35937', '7', 'Transfer the rice to a platter or bowl, garnish with the scallions, cilantro and pickled mustard greens and serve.'),
('35943', '1', 'Put eggs in a medium saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil over high heat. When water boils, cover, turn off heat, and let sit 14 minutes. Fill a large bowl with ice water.'),
('35943', '2', 'Transfer eggs to ice water and set aside.'),
('35943', '3', 'While eggs are cooking, in a second medium saucepan bring rice, salt, and 3 cups water to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook 15 minutes. Take off heat, still covered, and let sit 5 minutes.'),
('35943', '4', 'While rice is coming to a boil and eggs are sitting, mix together pork, sake, and 2 tbsp. tamari in a small bowl. Peel and grate ginger. Put 1 tbsp. ginger in with the pork. put remainder in a small bowl and set aside.'),
('35943', '5', 'While rice is cooking, peel and roughly chop garlic and chop green onions. add both to bowl of ginger. Trim woody ends off asparagus, cut into 1 1/2-in. pieces, and set aside.'),
('35943', '6', 'While rice is sitting, in a large frying pan over high heat add 1 tbsp. oil and pork mixture. Cook, stirring occasionally, until pork is cooked through, about 4 minutes. Meanwhile, fluff rice with a fork and divide evenly between 4 to 6 bowls and set them near the stove. Top rice with pork and pan juices, dividing evenly.'),
('35943', '7', 'Return pan to heat and add remaining 1 tbsp. oil, reserved ginger, garlic, and green onions. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('35943', '8', 'Add asparagus and remaining 1 tsp. tamari and stir to combine.'),
('35943', '9', 'Add broth, cover, and cook until asparagus is just tender to the bite, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('35943', '10', 'While asparagus cooks, pat eggs dry, peel, and cut into 1/4-in. slices. Divide asparagus and pan juices evenly between bowls of rice and pork. Top each serving with slices of egg and serve immediately.'),
('35945', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat.'),
('35945', '2', 'Add pork, and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or just until done.'),
('35945', '3', 'Add carrot and next 4 ingredients. stir-fry 2 minutes.'),
('35945', '4', 'Add cooked rice. stir-fry 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Push rice mixture to sides of pan, forming a well in center.'),
('35945', '5', 'Add egg to center of pan, and cook 30 seconds. toss with rice mixture, and stir-fry until egg is cooked. Stir in soy sauce and water. cook until thoroughly heated.'),
('35946', '1', 'Rinse rice with cold running water 3 minutes or until water is no longer cloudy.'),
('35946', '2', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('35946', '3', 'Cook bacon in a 3 1/2-qt. saucepan over medium heat 10 minutes or until crisp.'),
('35946', '4', 'Drain and set bacon aside, reserving 2 Tbsp. bacon drippings in pan.'),
('35946', '5', 'Saut onion in hot drippings in saucepan over medium-high heat 8 minutes or until onion is tender. add garlic, and saut 1 minute.'),
('35946', '6', 'Stir in rinsed rice, chicken broth, and next 3 ingredients. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low, and simmer 30 minutes, stirring mixture every 7 to 10 minutes.'),
('35946', '7', 'Remove from heat. fluff with a fork. Stir in crumbled bacon and 3 Tbsp. parsley. garnish, if desired.'),
('35953', '1', 'Cook rice according to package directions. cool 20 minutes.'),
('35953', '2', 'Stir together rice, artichoke hearts, and remaining ingredients.'),
('35953', '3', '*1 1/2 Tbsp. dried dill may be substituted for fresh.'),
('35954', '1', 'Combine shrimp, ginger, and crushed red pepper in a small bowl. let stand 5 minutes.'),
('35954', '2', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat.'),
('35954', '3', 'Add bell pepper, green onions, and garlic. stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until tender.'),
('35954', '4', 'Add shrimp mixture to pan. stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.'),
('35954', '5', 'Add cooked rice. stir-fry 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Push rice mixture to sides of pan, forming a well in center.'),
('35954', '6', 'Add egg to center of pan, and cook 30 seconds. toss with rice mixture, and stir-fry until egg is cooked. Stir in soy sauce and water. cook until thoroughly heated.'),
('35960', '1', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 1 minute. add eggs, and cook, gently stirring, 1 to 2 minutes or until softly scrambled.'),
('35960', '2', 'Remove eggs from skillet. chop.'),
('35960', '3', 'Heat remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in skillet. add onion, bell pepper, and green beans, and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.'),
('35960', '4', 'Add chicken, and stir-fry 2 minutes.'),
('35960', '5', 'Add rice, soy sauce, and chili-garlic sauce. stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir in scrambled eggs. sprinkle with desired toppings.'),
('35962', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('35962', '2', 'Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.'),
('35962', '3', 'Add 4 chicken thighs to pan. saut 3 minutes on each side or until browned.'),
('35962', '4', 'Remove chicken from pan. Repeat with remaining chicken.'),
('35962', '5', 'Add onion and carrot to pan. saut 4 minutes.'),
('35962', '6', 'Add mushrooms. saut 5 minutes.'),
('35962', '7', 'Add garlic. saut 1 minute, stirring constantly.'),
('35962', '8', 'Add rice. saut 1 minute. Spoon rice mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish coated with cooking spray. stir in broth, 1/4 cup water, and cream. Arrange chicken over rice mixture. sprinkle with cheese.'),
('35962', '9', 'Bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.'),
('35964', '1', 'Put rice in a pot and cover with an inch of cold water. Swish around until water is milky. pour off water. Repeat rinsing twice. then drain rice well in a colander and let dry 15 minutes.'),
('35964', '2', 'Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat.'),
('35964', '3', 'Add rice and cook, stirring, 2 minutes. then increase heat to medium and cook until rice starts to turn golden, 6 to 8 minutes, stirring often. Meanwhile, in a blender, pure onion, garlic, chile, and chopped tomatoes.'),
('35964', '4', 'Add tomato pure to rice, increase heat to high, and cook, stirring, until pure has been mostly absorbed, about 3 minutes (it will bubble and spatter). Stir in chicken broth and salt and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until all liquid is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('35964', '5', 'Let stand 10 minutes.'),
('35971', '1', 'Soak the rice in water for at least 2 hours.Wash the chicken and dry thoroughly with paper towels.'),
('35971', '2', 'Remove any excess bits of fat or skin then make the marinade by combining the yogurt, garam masala, coriander, cinnamon, garlic ginger, salt and pepper in a bowl. Thoroughly coat the chicken with the marinade, cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.'),
('35971', '3', 'Heat a pan over medium heat and add a generous splash of oil. Fry the onions and ginger along with a generous pinch of salt until the onions are are just starting to brown.'),
('35971', '4', 'Add the chilies and coconut and continue frying stirring constantly until the whole mixture is a nice golden brown. Taste and add additional salt to taste.'),
('35971', '5', 'Transfer to a bowl, scraping as much off the pan as you can.'),
('35971', '6', 'Heat 3 qts of water along with the salt, cinnamon, cardamom, cloves and bay leaf until the water is boiling and has taken on a brown color from the spices.'),
('35971', '7', 'Drain the soaking rice and add to the boiling water. Cover with a lid and cook for 5 minutes, stirring once.'),
('35971', '8', 'Drain the rice and pick out the spices.'),
('35971', '9', 'Heat a medium sauce pan that''s big enough to fit all the chicken in a single layer over medium heat.'),
('35971', '10', 'Add a splash of oil and fry the chicken until brown on one side (6 to 7 minutes). Flip and brown the other side.'),
('35971', '11', 'Transfer the chicken to a plate and drain off any excess oil.'),
('35971', '12', 'Add half the rice to the pan you fried the chicken in then spread the coconut/onion mixture over the rice. Cover with the rest of the rice and pour the coconut milk over the rice. Top with the chicken and any collected juices, cover the pot with a lid, and put over medium high heat. Once you hear the coconut milk boiling, turn the heat down to medium low and maintain a gentle simmer. Do not take the lid off while cooking as the trapped heat is necessary to cook the chicken. Simmer for about 20 minutes or until there is no liquid left.To serve, plate the rice making sure to get the middle and bottom layers and top with a piece of chicken. Finish with a sprinkle of Thai basil and serve with chutney or sambal.'),
('35972', '1', 'Cut chicken into 1/4-inch slices, and set aside.'),
('35972', '2', 'Heat rice according to package directions. set aside.'),
('35972', '3', 'Saut bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat 8 minutes or until crisp. remove bacon with a slotted spoon, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.'),
('35972', '4', 'Saut onion in hot drippings in skillet 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in chicken, and saut 8 minutes or until chicken is done. Stir in rice, bacon, peas, and next 3 ingredients. cook, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.'),
('35972', '5', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('35972', '6', '*4 ounces (about 1 heaping cup) snow peas may be substituted for green peas. Microwave snow peas and 1/4 cup water in a microwave-safe bowl 2 minutes before adding to chicken mixture. Proceed with recipe as directed.'),
('35972', '7', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Uncle Ben''s Original Long Grain Ready Rice.'),
('35975', '1', 'Fill the bottom of an Asian-style steamer with an inch or two of water, and bring it to a boil over high heat. (You can also use a collapsible Western-style steamer in a large saucepan.)'),
('35975', '2', 'Put the Chinese sausage on a plate, place the plate in the steamer, cover, and steam until the sausage is heated through, about 10 minutes.'),
('35975', '3', 'Transfer the sausage to a cutting board and slice it diagonally into 1/2-inch-thick pieces.'),
('35975', '4', 'Combine the shrimp, chicken, egg white, cornstarch, and the pinch of salt in a medium bowl.'),
('35975', '5', 'Mix well, and set aside.'),
('35975', '6', 'Heat a large wok over high heat.'),
('35975', '7', 'Add enough oil to come 1 inch up the sides of the wok, and heat it to 300F.'),
('35975', '8', 'Add the shrimp and chicken, and stir gently unto they turn white, about 45 seconds. Using a wide wire-mesh strainer, transfer the shrimp and chicken to a colander to drain. Discard all but 4 tablespoons of the oil from the wok.'),
('35975', '9', 'Return the wok with the oil to high heat, and heat until the oil is shimmering. Beat the whole eggs in a small bowl, and add to the wok. Scramble the eggs until they are quite firm and not runny, about 15 seconds.'),
('35975', '10', 'Transfer to a plate. Return the shrimp and chicken to the wok, and add the onions and the scallions. Stir-fry until the scallions soften, about 15 seconds.'),
('35975', '11', 'Add the sausage and peas, and stir-fry for 15 seconds.'),
('35975', '12', 'Add the rice, white pepper, and remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, and stir-fry until the rice is piping hot, about 3 minutes. Return the eggs to the wok and stir-fry for a few seconds.'),
('35975', '13', 'Serve immediately.'),
('35976', '1', 'Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan. add rice and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 18 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is done.'),
('35976', '2', 'Remove from heat. fluff with fork.'),
('35976', '3', 'Add 1/2 teaspoon salt, currants, and next 4 ingredients (currants through pepper). Cover. let stand 5 minutes.'),
('35976', '4', 'Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.'),
('35983', '1', 'Bring the broth and water to a boil in saucepan over medium heat. Reduce the heat to low and keep hot.'),
('35983', '2', 'In another saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.'),
('35983', '3', 'Add the scallions and cook for about 3 minutes. Stir in the rice, season with salt and pepper, to taste, and cook for another 2 minutes.'),
('35983', '4', 'Pour in the hot broth mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer and cover the saucepan. Cook until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Stir in walnuts and taste for seasoning, adjusting as necessary.'),
('35983', '5', 'Transfer the pilaf to a serving bowl and serve.'),
('35988', '1', 'Bring broth and coconut milk to a boil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat. add rice. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.'),
('35988', '2', 'Remove from heat. keep warm.'),
('35988', '3', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('35988', '4', 'Add onion. saut 5 minutes.'),
('35988', '5', 'Reduce heat to medium.'),
('35988', '6', 'Add squash. cook 8 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in thyme and remaining ingredients. cook 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.'),
('35988', '7', 'Add rice to squash mixture, stirring to combine.'),
('35995', '1', 'Melt the butter with the shallot in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat. Season with the salt and pepper and cook until the onions are soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('35995', '2', 'Add the rice and stir until coated with the butter. Increase the heat to medium-high.'),
('35995', '3', 'Let the rice cook until toasted, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes more.'),
('35995', '4', 'Stir in the broth, bay leaf, and rosemary. Bring to a simmer over low heat, cover, and cook until all the broth has been absorbed by the rice and the rice is tender, about 15 to 18 minutes.'),
('35995', '5', 'Remove from the heat and let set for 5 minutes. Discard the rosemary and bay leaf. Fluff the rice with a fork and serve.'),
('35996', '1', 'Melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('35996', '2', 'Add the onion and cook for 3 minutes.'),
('35996', '3', 'Add the rice and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low.'),
('35996', '4', 'Add the wine and cook, stirring frequently, until the liquid is absorbed.'),
('35996', '5', 'Add the broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring occasionally and waiting until it''s absorbed before adding more. It should take about 30 minutes for all the broth to be absorbed.'),
('35996', '6', 'Remove from heat and stir in the Parmesan, salt, and pepper. Spoon into individual bowls.'),
('36003', '1', 'Melt the butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('36003', '2', 'Add the onion and cook for 3 minutes.'),
('36003', '3', 'Add the rice and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Reduce heat to medium-low.'),
('36003', '4', 'Add the wine and cook, stirring frequently, until the liquid is absorbed.'),
('36003', '5', 'Add the broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring occasionally and waiting until it''s absorbed before adding more. It should take about 30 minutes for all the broth to be absorbed.'),
('36003', '6', 'Remove from heat and stir in the Parmesan, salt, and pepper, then stir in the pesto. Spoon into individual bowls.'),
('36004', '1', 'Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('36004', '2', 'Add the onion and cook for 3 minutes.'),
('36004', '3', 'Add the rice and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Reduce heat, add the wine, and cook, stirring frequently, until the liquid is absorbed.'),
('36004', '4', 'Add the broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring occasionally and waiting until its absorbed before adding more. This should take about 30 minutes total. The rice should be tender but still slightly firm.'),
('36004', '5', 'Remove from heat.'),
('36004', '6', 'Add the lemon juice, salt, pepper, Parmesan, and the remaining butter and stir until the butter melts. Spoon into individual bowls and sprinkle with the zest and parsley.'),
('36009', '1', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a medium, heavy nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('36009', '2', 'Add the onions and saute until translucent, about 3 minutes.'),
('36009', '3', 'Add the poblano chiles and saute, about 8 minutes.'),
('36009', '4', 'Mix in the garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Season with the salt and pepper.'),
('36009', '5', 'Add 1 cup broth and bring to a boil. Turn off the heat and let cool.'),
('36009', '6', 'Transfer the mixture to a blender and process until smooth, about 1 minute. Measure the liquid yield from the blender, adding more chicken broth if necessary to yield 2 total cups of poblano liquid. Adjust seasoning to taste.'),
('36009', '7', 'Meanwhile, clean the skillet, place over medium heat and add the remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Fry the rice until slightly golden.'),
('36009', '8', 'Pour the poblano puree into the skillet and bring to a simmer. Turn down the heat to medium-low and cover tightly. Cook for 30 minutes, turn off the heat and let rest for 10 minutes. Fluff with a fork before serving.'),
('36010', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('36010', '2', 'Add the onion and cook for 4 minutes.'),
('36010', '3', 'Add the rice and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.'),
('36010', '4', 'Add the wine and cook, stirring frequently, until the liquid is absorbed. Stir in the broth, 3/4 cup at a time (waiting until each addition of broth is absorbed before adding the next), and cook, stirring occasionally. It should take about 25 minutes for all the broth to be absorbed.'),
('36010', '5', 'Remove from heat and stir in the edamame, lemon zest, tarragon, 3/4 cup of the Parmesan, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Spoon into individual bowls and top with the remaining Parmesan. Shortcut: To thaw edamame and other frozen bagged vegetables quickly, place them in a colander or a mesh strainer and run them under cool water.'),
('36011', '1', 'Warm the broth in a small saucepan over low heat. Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('36011', '2', 'Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes or until soft.'),
('36011', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook 1 minute more.'),
('36011', '4', 'Add the barley and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Stir in the wine and cook until the liquid is absorbed, about 3 minutes.'),
('36011', '5', 'Add the broth, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring occasionally and waiting until it is absorbed before adding more.'),
('36011', '6', 'Add the asparagus with the last 1/2 cup of broth and cook until tender. It should take 30 to 35 minutes for all the broth to be absorbed.'),
('36011', '7', 'Remove from heat, season with the salt and pepper, and stir in the Parmesan. Spoon into individual bowls.Tip: At the store, look for thick or thin asparagus with firm stalks, closed tips, and a bright green color.'),
('36034', '1', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 1 minute. add eggs, and cook, gently stirring, 1 to 2 minutes or until softly scrambled.'),
('36034', '2', 'Remove eggs from skillet. chop.'),
('36034', '3', 'Heat remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in skillet. add onion, bell pepper, and green beans, and stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.'),
('36034', '4', 'Add chicken, and stir-fry 2 minutes.'),
('36034', '5', 'Add rice, soy sauce, and chili-garlic sauce. stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir in scrambled eggs. sprinkle with desired toppings.'),
('36042', '1', 'In a 2- to 3-quart pan over high heat, bring 6 1/2 cups broth to a simmer. cover and reduce heat to maintain simmer.'),
('36042', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a food processor, whirl basil, garlic, and 1 teaspoon olive oil until coarsely chopped.'),
('36042', '3', 'Add cheese and whirl until finely ground.'),
('36042', '4', 'Add remaining 2 teaspoons oil and the butter to a 5- to 6-quart pan over medium-high heat. when hot (mixture will be foamy), add shallots and stir often until limp, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('36042', '5', 'Add rice and stir often until beginning to turn opaque, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('36042', '6', 'Add wine and stir until absorbed, about 1 minute.'),
('36042', '7', 'Add 6 cups broth, 1 cup at a time, stirring after each addition until almost absorbed, 25 to 30 minutes total. Stir in basil mixture and cook, stirring often, until rice is barely tender to bite and mixture is creamy, about 2 minutes longer. If risotto is thicker than desired, stir in a little more broth.'),
('36042', '8', 'Ladle risotto into wide, shallow bowls, and serve immediately.'),
('36043', '1', 'Bring chicken broth to a simmer in a medium pot. Keep at a simmer, covered, over low heat.'),
('36043', '2', 'Heat the olive oil and 2 tbsp. butter over medium heat in a heavy-bottomed 8-qt. pot.'),
('36043', '3', 'Add onion and saut, stirring occasionally, until translucent and beginning to turn golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('36043', '4', 'Add rice and saut, stirring constantly, until just the edges of the grains look translucent, about 3 minutes.'),
('36043', '5', 'Add wine and 1/2 tsp. salt and cook, stirring, until wine is completely absorbed by rice.'),
('36043', '6', 'Add about 1/2 cup hot broth to rice and cook, stirring constantly, until broth is completely absorbed by rice. reduce heat to medium-low if mixture starts to boil. Continue adding broth 1/2 cup at a time, stirring until each addition is absorbed before adding the next, until rice is just tender to the bite (15 to 30 minutes. you will have broth left over). Keep rice at a constant simmer.'),
('36043', '7', 'Remove rice from heat and stir in parmesan, pepper, parsley, remaining 1 tsp. butter, and salt to taste. For a looser risotto, stir in 1 to 2 cups remaining broth.'),
('36043', '8', 'Serve immediately, with more parmesan on the side for sprinkling.'),
('36043', '9', '*For a recipe, go to sunset.com/chickenbroth'),
('36044', '1', 'Pour oil into a 5- to 6-quart pan over medium-high heat. when hot, add onion and mushrooms and stir often until onion is limp and liquid has evaporated, 5 to 6 minutes.'),
('36044', '2', 'Add rice and stir until opaque, about 3 minutes.'),
('36044', '3', 'Add wine and stir until it''s absorbed, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('36044', '4', 'Add 4 1/2 cups broth and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring often. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring often until rice is tender to bite, 15 to 20 minutes. If a creamier consistency is desired, stir in about 1/2 cup more broth. Stir in cheese, parsley, sage, tarragon, and thyme.'),
('36044', '5', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('36044', '6', 'Cleaning mushrooms: Trim off tough or discolored bottoms of mushroom stems and any bruised spots or blemishes. (For shiitakes and oysters, remove the entire fibrous stem.) For firm mushrooms such as portabellas, wipe dirt off with a damp cloth or place in a colander, rinse thoroughly under cool running water, and pat dry with towels. For delicate mushrooms that have lots of places for dirt to hide, such as chanterelles and hedgehogs, submerge in a bowl of cool water and gently agitate with you hands to loose any particles.'),
('36044', '7', 'Drain, rinse carefully under running water, and gently pat dry with a towel.'),
('36047', '1', 'In a small saucepan, bring broth to a simmer.'),
('36047', '2', 'Heat oil in a large pot.'),
('36047', '3', 'Add onions and rice and cook, stirring, until rice is browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in broth, 1/2 cup at a time, and cook, stirring constantly until almost all the broth is absorbed before adding more, until rice is al dente, about 20 minutes. add hot water if you need more liquid. About 5 minutes before rice is done, add asparagus, butter, and parmesan and cook until asparagus is tender-crisp.'),
('36050', '1', 'Warm oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('36050', '2', 'Add onion and bacon and cook, stirring often, until starting to brown.'),
('36050', '3', 'Add rice to pan and stir to coat in oil.'),
('36050', '4', 'Pour in wine and cook until evaporated, about 3 minutes.'),
('36050', '5', 'Mix 2 cups hot water into broth and stir into rice in 1/2-cup increments (let each absorb before adding next). Stir, adding more hot water if needed, until rice is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('36050', '6', 'Remove from heat and quickly stir in cheeses, salt, and pepper. Top with a sprinkle of chives.'),
('36051', '1', 'Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a 12-inch frying pan over high heat.'),
('36051', '2', 'Add 12 ounces sliced mushrooms and 3/4 cup chopped shallots or onion. cook, stirring often, until mushrooms are lightly browned, 9 to 12 minutes.'),
('36051', '3', 'Reduce heat to medium and add 2 more tablespoons butter and 2 cups dried orzo pasta. stir often until pasta is light golden, about 2 minutes.'),
('36051', '4', 'Add 3 cups chicken broth and 1/2 cup dry sherry. Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring often, until pasta is tender to bite and most of the liquid is absorbed, 9 to 11 minutes. If mixture becomes too thick before pasta is done, add a little more broth.'),
('36051', '5', 'Stir in 1/3 cup grated parmesan cheese and salt and pepper to taste. Spoon risotto into wide bowls and sprinkle with a little chopped parsley and more parmesan cheese to taste.'),
('36064', '1', 'In a rice cooker, mix the rice, stock, water, and 1 tablespoon butter. Cover and cook according to machine instructions. Meanwhile, in a small saute pan over low heat, saute the onion in the remaining 3 tablespoons butter until soft and sweet, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Set aside. When the rice is done, toss the rice with the onion butter and serve..'),
('36072', '1', 'Heat oven to 400 F. In a large bowl, combine the rice, tomatoes and their juices, broth, orange juice, parsley, onion, garlic, cumin, 3/4 teaspoon of the salt, 1/4 teaspoon of the black pepper, and the red pepper (if using).'),
('36072', '2', 'Transfer to a 9-by-13-inch baking dish. Rinse the chicken and pat dry. Season with the remaining salt and pepper. Nestle the chicken pieces among the rice mixture. Cover the dish tightly with foil.'),
('36072', '3', 'Bake until the chicken is cooked through, about 35 minutes.'),
('36072', '4', 'Remove from oven.'),
('36072', '5', 'Let stand for 5 minutes. Spoon the rice and chicken into individual bowls. Sprinkle with additional parsley.Tip: Stick with ordinary long-grain rice in recipes that include several other flavors. Save aromatic varieties of rice, like basmati and jasmine, for those nights when you want an easy, flavorful side dish thats impressive all by itself.'),
('36074', '1', 'Combine shrimp, ginger, and crushed red pepper in a small bowl. let stand 5 minutes.'),
('36074', '2', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over high heat.'),
('36074', '3', 'Add bell pepper, green onions, and garlic. stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes or until tender.'),
('36074', '4', 'Add shrimp mixture to pan. stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.'),
('36074', '5', 'Add cooked rice. stir-fry 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Push rice mixture to sides of pan, forming a well in center.'),
('36074', '6', 'Add egg to center of pan, and cook 30 seconds. toss with rice mixture, and stir-fry until egg is cooked. Stir in soy sauce and water. cook until thoroughly heated.'),
('36084', '1', 'In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil.'),
('36084', '2', 'Add the sausage and cook over high heat, breaking up the meat with a spoon, until browned, about 5 minutes.'),
('36084', '3', 'Add the fennel and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, about 8 minutes longer. Cover and keep warm.'),
('36084', '4', 'In a medium saucepan, bring the chicken stock to a simmer. keep warm.'),
('36084', '5', 'In a large saucepan, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('36084', '6', 'Add the onion, season with salt and pepper and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('36084', '7', 'Add the rice and cook, for 1 minute stirring constantly to thoroughly coat it with the fat. Crumble the saffron into the wine and add it to the rice. Cook, stirring until the wine is absorbed.'),
('36084', '8', 'Add 1 cup of the warm stock and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until nearly absorbed. Continue adding the stock 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly, until it is nearly absorbed between additions. The risotto is done when the rice is al dente and suspended in a thick, creamy sauce, about 20 minutes total. Season the risotto with salt and pepper. Stir in the sausage and fennel along with the cheese, butter and parsley.'),
('36084', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('36085', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, combine the clam broth and water and bring to a simmer. Keep warm.'),
('36085', '2', 'In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil.'),
('36085', '3', 'Add the onion, season with salt and pepper and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('36085', '4', 'Add the rice and cook for 1 minute, stirring to thoroughly coat. Crumble the saffron into the wine and add it to the rice. Cook, stirring until the wine is absorbed.'),
('36085', '5', 'Add 1 cup of the warm clam juice and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until nearly absorbed. Continue adding the juice 1/2 cup at a time, and stirring constantly until it is nearly absorbed between additions. The risotto is done when the rice is al dente and suspended in a thick, creamy sauce, about 20 minutes total. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('36085', '6', 'Melt the butter in a large skillet.'),
('36085', '7', 'Add the shallot and cook over moderate heat until softened, about 2 minutes.'),
('36085', '8', 'Add the shrimp and crab and cook until just heated through. Scrape the seafood into the risotto and stir in the parsley and mascarpone.'),
('36085', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('36087', '1', 'In a 12-inch frying pan with 2-inch-tall sides or a 5-quart pan over medium-high heat, stir bacon until browned and crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('36087', '2', 'Transfer to paper towels to drain. Discard all but about 1/2 tablespoon bacon fat from pan.'),
('36087', '3', 'Add 2 tablespoons olive oil to pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add onion, garlic, salt, and pepper. Reduce heat to medium and stir frequently until onion is very soft and browned, 20 to 25 minutes (if onion starts to scorch, reduce heat further and stir in 2 tablespoons water).'),
('36087', '4', 'Meanwhile, rinse chard. Trim and discard stem ends. Thinly slice stems crosswise and coarsely chop leaves. In a 5- to 6-quart pan over high heat, bring about 3 quarts water to a boil.'),
('36087', '5', 'Add chard and cook, stirring occasionally, until stems are tender-crisp to bite, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('36087', '6', 'Drain, place in a large bowl of ice water until cool, and drain again.'),
('36087', '7', 'Add rice to onions and stir until opaque, about 3 minutes.'),
('36087', '8', 'Add wine and stir over medium heat until absorbed, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('36087', '9', 'Add 6 cups broth, a cup at a time, stirring after each addition until almost absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes total (rice should be tender to bite).'),
('36087', '10', 'Stir in cheese, butter, bacon, chard, and roasted mushrooms. If risotto is thicker than desired, stir in a little more broth. Spoon risotto into wide, shallow bowls.'),
('36108', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Season the duck legs well with salt and pepper. When the skillet is hot, add the duck pieces, skin-side down and sear until lightly browned, about 5 minutes per side.'),
('36108', '2', 'Drain the fat.'),
('36108', '3', 'Transfer the legs to a medium pot and add enough of the stock to cover, and then simmer, covered, over low heat, until the meat is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.'),
('36108', '4', 'Meanwhile, drain the duck fat from the skillet, add the sausage, and saute the over medium heat until the fat is rendered, about 5 minutes.'),
('36108', '5', 'Remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain and wipe out the skillet.'),
('36108', '6', 'Transfer the duck legs to a plate. When cool enough to handle, remove the skin, pull the meat from the bones, and shred into bite-size pieces. Set aside. Spoon the fat from the top of the stock and add the remaining stock into the pot. Bring to a simmer over medium-low heat.'),
('36108', '7', 'Heat the oven to 160F and slip in a cooling rack set on a baking sheet.'),
('36108', '8', 'With a razor-sharp knife, score the skin of the breast in a crosshatch pattern, being mindful not to cut into the flesh. Pat dry and season with salt and pepper.'),
('36108', '9', 'Heat a large dry skillet over medium-low heat, add the breast, skin-side down, and sear until crisp, allowing the fat to render slowly, 10 to 15 minutes. Don''t rush this. The last thing you want is a mouthful of chewy fat. Flip and sear the other side for 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('36108', '10', 'Transfer the duck to the rack in the oven to keep warm.'),
('36108', '11', 'Drain all but 3 tablespoons of fat from the skillet and heat over medium heat.'),
('36108', '12', 'Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the rice to coat, and cook until translucent around the edges, about 2 minutes. Splash in the wine and continue cooking until absorbed.'),
('36108', '13', 'Add a ladleful of hot stock and cook, stirring continuously, until the liquid has almost burbled away. Keep up this rhythm of adding stock, stirring, and cooking for 15 minutes.'),
('36108', '14', 'Stir in the ham, sausage, and the shredded pieces of duck into the risotto and resume ladling, stirring, and cooking until the rice moves wave-like when mounded and is tender but offers just the slightest bit of resistance in the middle, 5 to 10 minutes more. Stir in the orange juice and butter and season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('36108', '15', 'Cut the breast crosswise into thin slices. To serve, divide the risotto among shallow bowls and arrange the slices on top. Sprinkle with the parsley and orange zest. Rush to the table.'),
('36112', '1', 'Heat 1 tbsp. oil and 1 tbsp. butter over medium heat in a medium heavy-bottomed pot. add carrots and stir with a wooden spoon until well coated.'),
('36112', '2', 'Add 1/2 cup water, 1/2 tsp. salt, and the sugar. cover and cook 5 minutes, or until tender. Uncover and cook, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates and carrots are just starting to brown, a few minutes more. Reserve half of the carrots. In a blender, pure other half with 3/4 cup hot water.');